The Clear-completed button is present in the DOM but carries the `hidden` class,
so it is not shown and the ` | [Clear completed]` segment is absent. This is how
the app hides the button when no completed todo exists.
Pins: the Clear-completed segment is read from `.clear-completed` shown-ness, and
`hidden` counts as not shown.

-- dom.html --
<section class="todoapp">
	<header class="header">
		<h1>todos</h1>
		<input class="new-todo" placeholder="What needs to be done?">
	</header>
	<section class="main">
		<input id="toggle-all" class="toggle-all" type="checkbox">
		<label for="toggle-all">Mark all as complete</label>
		<ul class="todo-list">
			<li data-id="t1">
				<div class="view">
					<input class="toggle" type="checkbox">
					<label>buy milk</label>
					<button class="destroy"></button>
				</div>
				<input class="edit" value="buy milk">
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
	<footer class="footer">
		<span class="todo-count"><strong>1</strong> item left</span>
		<ul class="filters">
			<li><a class="selected" href="/">All</a></li>
			<li><a href="/active">Active</a></li>
			<li><a href="/completed">Completed</a></li>
		</ul>
		<button class="clear-completed hidden">Clear completed</button>
	</footer>
</section>

-- projection.txt --
v > ""
#t1 [ ] buy milk
-- **1** item left | (All) Active Completed
